            <exercise>
                <statement>
                    <p>A certain water heater will cost you <m>\$900</m> to buy and have installed. This water heater claims that its operating expense (money spent on electricity or gas) will be about <m>\$31</m> per month. According to this information, the equation <m>y=900+31x</m> models the total cost of the water heater after <m>x</m> months. Make a table of at least five values and plot a graph of this equation.</p>
                </statement>
                <solution>
                    <p>We'll include <m>x=0</m> representing the total expense right after buying and installing the equipment. Then we'll use some <m>x</m>-values several months and years into the future.</p>
                    <sidebyside>
                        <table>
                            <caption>Make the table</caption>
                            <tabular valign="top" bottom="minor">
                                <col halign="right" right="minor"/>
                                <col halign="center" right="minor"/>
                                <col halign="center"/>
                                <row bottom="medium">
                                    <cell><m>x</m></cell>
                                    <cell halign="center"><m>y</m></cell>
                                    <cell>Point</cell>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <cell><m>0</m></cell>
                                    <cell><m>900</m></cell>
                                    <cell><m>(0,900)</m></cell>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <cell><m>1</m></cell>
                                    <cell><m>931</m></cell>
                                    <cell><m>(1,931)</m></cell>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <cell><m>6</m></cell>
                                    <cell><m>1086</m></cell>
                                    <cell><m>(6,1086)</m></cell>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <cell><m>12</m></cell>
                                    <cell><m>1272</m></cell>
                                    <cell><m>(12,1272)</m></cell>
                                </row>
                                <row bottom="none">
                                    <cell><m>24</m></cell>
                                    <cell><m>1644</m></cell>
                                    <cell><m>(24,1644)</m></cell>
                                </row>
                            </tabular>
                        </table>
                        <figure>
                            <caption>Make the graph</caption>
                            <image>
                                <latex-image-code>
                                    <![CDATA[\begin{tikzpicture}
                                        \begin{axis}[xmin=0,xmax=30,
                                                    ymin=0,ymax=2000,
                                                    xlabel={$x$ (months)},
                                                    ylabel={$y$ (dollars)},
                                                    xtick={0,6,...,30},
                                                    minor xtick={0,1,...,30},
                                                    ytick=,
                                                    minor ytick={0,100,...,2000},
                                                    clip=false,
                                                    axis line style={->}]
                                            \addplot+[domain=0:30,->] {900+31*x};
                                            \addplot[soliddot] coordinates {(0,900)};% node[below right,rotate=-30]{$(0,900)$};
                                            \addplot[soliddot] coordinates {(1,931)} node[below right,rotate=-30]{$(1,931)$};
                                            \addplot[soliddot] coordinates {(6,1086)} node[below right,rotate=-30]{$(6,1086)$};
                                            \addplot[soliddot] coordinates {(12,1272)} node[below right,rotate=-30]{$(12,1272)$};;
                                            \addplot[soliddot] coordinates {(24,1644)} node[below right,rotate=-30]{$(24,1644)$};;
                                        \end{axis}
                                    \end{tikzpicture}
                                    ]]>
                                </latex-image-code>
                            </image>
                        </figure>
                    </sidebyside>
                </solution>
            </exercise>
            <exercise>
                <statement>
                    <p>You bought a new Toyota Corolla for <m>\$18{,}600</m> with a zero interest loan over a five-year period. That means you'll have to pay <m>\$310</m> each month for the next five years (sixty months) to pay it off. According to this information, the equation <m>y=18600-310x</m> models the loan balance after <m>x</m> months. Make a table of at least five values and plot a graph of this equation. Make sure to include a data point representing when you will have paid off the loan.</p>
